%N A397198 Decimal expansion of Sum_{k>=1} (-1)^(k+1)*H(2*k,4)/k, where H(k,4) = A007410(k)/A007480(k) is the k-th harmonic number of order 4.
%H A397198 Cornel Ioan Vălean, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-031-21262-8">More (Almost) Impossible Integrals, Sums, and Series</a>, Springer Cham, 2023. See section 4.22, p. 425.
%H A397198 <a href="/index/Ha#harmonic">Index entries for sequences related to harmonic numbers</a>.
%F A397198 Equals 4*zeta(5) - 3*zeta(2)*zeta(3)/128 - 7*log(2)*zeta(4)/128 + Pi^5/192 - Pi^3*G/16 - Pi*polygamma(3, 1/4)/1536, where G is Catalan's constant (A006752), and polygamma(3, 1/4) = psi'''(1/4) is the third derivative of the digamma function at 1/4 (A390074).
%e A397198 0.731867744437270599431349028033439241386718878385845...
%t A397198 RealDigits[4*Zeta[5] - 3*Zeta[2]*Zeta[3]/128 - 7*Log[2]*Zeta[4]/128 + Pi^5/192 - Pi^3*Catalan/16 - Pi*PolyGamma[3, 1/4]/1536, 10, 120][[1]]
